\forall A\in\mathcal{F}: \mathbb{P}(A)\in\left\{0,1\right\}
\mathbb{E}(f|\mathcal{F})=\mathbb{E}(f)
 \forall A\in\mathcal{F}: \int_A\mathbb{E}(f)\, d\mathbb{P}=\int_Af\, d\mathbb{P}. 
\mathcal{F}=\left\{\Omega,\emptyset\right\}
 \int_{\emptyset}\mathbb{E}(f)\, d\mathbb{P}=0=\int_{\emptyset}f\, d\mathbb{P},~~~~~\int_{\Omega}\mathbb{E}(f)\, d\mathbb{P}=\mathbb{E}(f)\mathbb{P}(\Omega)=\mathbb{E}(f)=\int_{\Omega}f\, d\mathbb{P}. 
